latestIgtvVideos.title: Pampering Session @bnbsalonandnails
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey guyss! 
It had been a long time since I had gotten a haircut and I badly needed one. Due to the current situation I was a little sceptical about going to a salon and getting my hair trimmed. But @bnbsalonandnails ensured that they would take proper care of all the safety measures. 
As I entered the salon, they checked my temperature and then gave me their gloves and a mask. All the employees present there were dressed in proper PPEs and Before using the  products were properly sanitised.
The quality of service at bnb was as usual perfect and professional. The stylist gave me personal haircare tips after looking at my hair type and over all  it was a very therapeutic experience. 
Thank you @bnbsalonandnails for such an amazing papering session. .
📸: Also, shoutout to @kathanadhyaru for filming and editing this video, go follow him guys. He’s a great and experienced photographer/videographer.
.
.
Let me know in the comment section about  what you think about my hair💇🏻‍♀️
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: 5 formal Outfit Ideas
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey guyss!! So here are 5 western formal looks that I have put together that can be worn at formal events or office, internships etc. In all these looks, I made sure that there are pants as bottoms so that the looks are more wearable and comfortable. Tried to keep them stylish, classy and different. 
I have given names to all these looks as per my interpretations: 
1. Office Fashionista: 
A trendy Monochrome look with checks pant and checks vest with black heels and watch. Added a black belt for a better look. Checks on checks looks very formal. This look is one of my favourites.
Pants: @shein_in 
Vest: @soliverfashion 
Heels: @inc5shoes 
Bag : @forever21_in 
Watch: @skagendenmark 
2. The Effortless look: 
In this look, I wore a simple white shirt on the checks pants. It takes minimum efforts and yet looks classy. 
Shirt: @hm 
3. The “not so formal” formal look: For a creative department empoyee or anyone who wants keep it formal and informal at the same time. 
So, in this look I wanted it to go creative. I wore white pants and a blue lining shirt. Tucked in the shirt from front but not the back. For a funky look I added a bow tie to it and took a light blue purse!! Shirt:  @nautica 
Pants: @veromodaindia 
Bag: @mango 
4. The BO$$ BABE: 
The classy 3 piece suit goggles and a classy bag. A professional office look. 
Goggles: @shein_in 
Bag: @hermes 
5. The Girl Next Door Look
Wanted to keep this look very elegant. Wore a ruffly white shirt and baby pink pants. Added a golden-silver watch and pearl jewellery to add an elegant touch to it. 
Necklace: @aldo_shoes 
Heels: @shein_in 
Which one is your favourite look out of the 5? Let me know in the comment section. .
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Indo-Western Outfit Ideas✨
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey guys 
I have always had a thing for indo- western outfits. They are so stylish and at the same time traditional .  To make normal day to day outfit into indo-western you can simply add jewellery or accessories. .
So here are 5 easy indo western outfits that you can wear. .
.
.
Comment your fav look in the comment section
.

Look 1
Wore an open peplum top @goa_paris on denim shorts and added indian jewellery and a black-gold clutch.
.
.

Look 2
My favourite look. A ghaghra and a simple Tshirt. Added a denim jacket and a traditional footwear. .
.

Look 3
A white chicken kurta and a bootcut pants @truereligion .I absolutely love this combination. Added jhumka for a perfect look. You can also add a scarf to this look, i chose not to. .
.

Look 4
Linen long dress with indian jewellery and a shirt. Added a belt, heels and bag. Its conservative yet stylish you can wear it in a semi-traditional function and even at a mall.
.
.

Look 5
This is a gamthi blouse that i wear in navratri. You can wear both a denim pant or pallazo pants under it.  It looksso indian yet western. .
.
.
.
